    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style and culture of the Arabatchi tribe. Typical of the style are rugs  characterized by a dark brown field, a part cotton weft and alternate warps which cause the back of the rugs to have a brown and white, speckled appearance.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
